  "prompt": "How much did it cost Samsung to make the Galaxy S5 waterproof?",
  "response": "The exact cost for Samsung to make the Galaxy S5 waterproof hasn't been disclosed publicly, and specific figures related to manufacturing costs for such features are generally proprietary information. However, incorporating waterproofing typically involves additional engineering, use of specialized materials, and modifications in design, which can increase the overall production cost.\n\nIn general, waterproofing a smartphone can involve features such as better seals, coatings for circuit boards, and more robust materials, which may add a small percentage to the overall manufacturing cost. Analysts have speculated that the cost increase might range from a few dollars to potentially around 10% of the total device's production cost, but these are just estimates.\n\nFor the most accurate and detailed information, one would typically refer to industry analysis reports or teardown studies conducted by tech analysts.",
